<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057112-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 8 and A = 25 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>17.2</li><li>18.9</li><li>65.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}=\frac{{8}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{8}}{{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{17.156055364076}\approx{17.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{17.156055364076}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={64}+{294.33023565526}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={358.33023565526}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{358.33023565526}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{18.92961266522}\approx{18.9}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{25}^{\circ}\approx{65}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>